The paper deals with decidability of observational equivalence for a fragment of a programming language, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. The use of game semantics and automata over data words suggests a connection to logic and verification (cs.LO), while the focus on call-by-value and references suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The mention of undecidability results also suggests a connection to complexity theory (cs.FL). The use of higher-order types and the identification of specific subfragments suggests a connection to type theory (cs.TL) and lambda calculus (cs.LT).
